  "text": "Today, the Solar wind's shape within a few AU of the Sun is well-described as an azimuthally-symmetric expansion of plasma, at velocity v sw and density ρ sw [CITATION_1] . However, on a larger scale (10s of AU), the on-coming ram pressure of the interstellar medium sculpts the heliosphere into a highly asymmetric, teardrop shape, with the direction of relative motion roughly aligned with the local interstellar magnetic field direction [CITATION_2] .",
